I don't think so either.

00:09:06.639 --> 00:09:11.341
What I'm driving at here is the
notion of minimum efficient

00:09:11.341 --> 00:09:11.990
scale.
 

00:09:11.990 --> 00:09:17.272
Capital gets--a resource gets
to be capital only when it's

00:09:17.272 --> 00:09:22.369
aggregated to a scale where it
can be effectively enough

00:09:22.369 --> 00:09:26.538
deployed to compete in an actual
economy.

00:09:26.538 --> 00:09:33.610
Now let's take--that's too big
a note, let's take a dollar.

00:09:33.610 --> 00:09:42.450
